      {
        "parameters": {
          "content": "## Wates AI Draft — n8n feeds the sketch, container draws\n\n**Flow:** poll the Plans inbox → pull the N-number → take the first image attachment → download it → SSH-upload it to the server `/tmp` → `docker cp` into the **plangenration** container → `docker exec … src/process_plan.py \"<N>\" --image /tmp/<file>` → mark the email read on success.\n\nThe container does the gating and the work: Wates **AND** status **Scheduled** → draw floors → upload VSDX to the AT yellow folder + SharePoint → status → **Plans Drawn**. It never reads the mailbox; n8n supplies the image.\n\n### Credentials\n- Outlook: **Plans-Acornhealthandsafety**\n- SSH: **Acorn n8n Server SSH**\n\n### ⚠️ Verify in the UI (SSH file node schema varies by version)\nOn **Upload sketch (SSH)**: Resource = File, Operation = Upload, Input Binary Field = `data`, Target Directory = `/tmp`. The SSH user must be able to write `/tmp` (n8nuser cannot write /opt/acorn — that is why we use /tmp).\n\n### Mark-read rule\nThe container prints ONE JSON line. stdout matching `\"ok\": true` or `\"skipped\": true` → mark read; anything else → leave unread to retry next poll.",
          "height": 440,
          "width": 480
        },
        "id": "05adf326-9b6b-4e0a-bd35-e9baa21715f1",
